cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the problem of effectively self-training neural networks in a low-resource setting for sequence labeling tasks such as Chunking and NER. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the development of algorithms that can learn from and make predictions on data. The paper also deals with natural language processing tasks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for handling noisy labels, which is a common problem in machine learning, suggesting that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
